section.section:
"Rigid plastic container" means any formed or molded container, other than a bottle that:
Is intended for single use;
Is predominantly composed of plastic resin;
Has a relatively inflexible finite shape or form; and
Has a capacity of at least 8 ounces but less than 5 gallons.

The numbering and lettering shall be as follows:
For polyethylene terepthalate, the letters "PETE" and the number 1;
For high density polyethylene, the letters "HDPE" and the number 2;
For vinyl, the letter "V" and the number 3;
For low density polyethylene, the letters "LDPE" and the number 4;
For polypropylene, the letters "PP" and the number 5;
For polystyrene, the letters "PS" and the number 6; and
For any other plastic resin, the word "Other" and the number 7.
